05/04/2005
TUNCELI, Turkey -- One soldier and nine Kurdish rebels were killed in new clashes between security forces and the outlawed separatist organisation KONGRA-GEL, according to reports from authorities in Sirnak province. 
Turkish security forces started operations in Sirnak five days ago, with the aim of eliminating a group of Kurdish militants in the area bordering Iraq. 
Officials say a large amount of weapons and ammunition has been seized.
In other news, an IMF mission arrived in Turkey on Monday for a new series of talks on the stand-by arrangement with the government. 
Local media reports that the Fund has agreed to discuss the possible revision of the $10 billion agreement initially reached in December. 
(NTV - 05/04/05; Reuters, TurkishPress.com - 04/04/05)
